begin_memory_text: At the beginning of the conversation, we spoke about other people with whom we talked. In addition, we talked about our area - we coincidentally live in the same county a few cities apart.
middle_memory_text: Our conversation then shifted to discussing hiking, cooking, and movies. I asked where she likes hiking, what recent recipes she's tried, and what movies she remembers liking.
end_memory_text: The last part of our conversation was the main focus - her preparation as a pharmacy student, what she expects to happen in the upcoming winter break, and my experience with organic chemistry in college four years ago.
rest_of_day_open: I see it going ok. My main reoccupation is figuring out my exercise now that it is going to get darker and colder more quickly. I feel like work this week won't be too stressful and everything else will be fine, though. I am excited for Halloween with my girlfriend.
critical_positive: I think shifting around different topics until we came to one for which my partner could contribute worked well. Sometimes you can't expect to stick with an initial conversation topic and have that be the focus the entire time, especially if the other person is not interested in it. Once I realized I could get her to talk about her pharmacy studies, I knew that could be a lasting conversation.
critical_negative: Although there were multiple times that my conversation partner helped move the conversation along, I felt like I had to guide it myself, lest I wanted there to be silence. Granted, silence in conversation is not automatically a bad thing but I was worried it might be perceived as such.

begin_memory_text: We talked about where we were from and what we liked to do for fun. We also talked about hiking trails in our area.
middle_memory_text: I think we talked about what we do for work/school and how that's been like during COVID. I'd say it has been pretty difficult for us adjusting to the changes but even more so for me.
end_memory_text: We talked about undergrad and how courses were like for us. We both had a different experience since we appear to have gone to different schools. We definitely agree that organic chemistry was a tough course.
rest_of_day_open: I see myself trying to study for my exams by going over the study guides that my friends and I have made. I also will probably work on assignments as well and take breaks by making myself yummy snacks and drinking ice coffee or tea. My breaks probably include watching funny dramas.
critical_positive: I think it worked well when my partner seemed to notice that we had so much in common and would emphasize what a coincidence nearly every time we talked. I thought that was so funny. It definitely helped that we were from the same area so we had lots more to talk more about things in the area.
critical_negative: I think there was a time when we ran out of things to talk about so the sound went quiet for a bit. I think it started to pick up when we asked each other questions that we had an automatic answer for and we knew exactly what to say.
